        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Shift Back to Society Act of </b><b>2017</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Justice to establish a pilot program that awards matching grants to historically black colleges and universities to provide educational programs for eligible offenders to facilitate re-entry into the community. </p> <p>An eligible offender is a convicted criminal offender who has been released from incarceration for less than one year or who is scheduled to be released from incarceration within one year.</p> <p>The Government Accountability Office must report to Congress on the results of the pilot program.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
